'''Kelley Lee Moore''' (born March 5, 1969) is an American television personality, [[event planner]] and [[author]]. She hosts the program ''Moore to Life'' (Canceled) ''So Much Moore''

(Canceled) and appeared on the local [[KING-TV]] program ''New Day Northwest''.<ref>http://www.king5.com/new-day-northwest</ref> Her other appearances have include [[HGTV]], [[The Ellen DeGeneres Show|Ellen]], [[The Today Show]], [[The View (U.S. TV series)|The View]], [[Rachael Ray]], and [[Tyra Banks]]. She wrote the book, ''Cube Chic: Take Your Office Space from Drab to Fab'' <ref>https://www.amazon.com/Cube-Chic-Take-Office-Space/dp/1594741050</ref> and was the Entertaining [[Columnist]] for ''[[Seattle Magazine]]''.<ref>http://www.seattlemag.com/pages/index.cfm?PAGE_ID=15&PERSON_ID=21</ref>

==Career==
Moore began writing stories about the Northwest for ''Seattle Magazine'' <ref>http://www.seattlemag.com/pages/index.cfm?PAGE_ID=15&PERSON_ID=21</ref> and ''Northwest Home'' in 2003. Since then, she has appeared on King 5 News and [[KONG (TV)|KONG TV]], with design, style, and entertaining tips. Her television show, ''Moore to Life'',<ref>http://www.seattlemag.com/pages/index.cfm?PAGE_ID=15&PERSON_ID=21</ref> debuted in 2009 on Seattle’s affiliate King 5 TV. And, in the fall of 2009, she appeared as one of three designers on [[HGTV]]’s, ''Halloween Block Party''.<ref>http://www.hgtv.com/halloween-block-party/show/index.html</ref>

Moore has written one book, ''Cube Chic: Take Your Office Space from Drab to Fab'',<ref>https://www.amazon.com/Cube-Chic-Take-Office-Space/dp/1594741050</ref> and is currently working on her second, ''Design from the Inside Out'',<ref>http://www.kelleylmoore.com/press-kit</ref> due to release in 2010.

